// Semantic direction:
// korteste_sti finds minimum-weight paths between vertices in a weighted graph.
// csr_graf (Compressed Sparse Row) stores graphs memory-efficiently: csr_rader[v] gives the edge range.
// dijkstra uses a priority queue to greedily expand the nearest unvisited vertex.
// dij_slapp_av updates the tentative distance if a shorter path through the current vertex is found.
// dij_fib_heap achieves O(E + V log V) with Fibonacci heap vs O((V+E) log V) for binary heap.
// bellman_ford relaxes all edges V-1 times, tolerating negative edge weights.
// spfa_queue (Shortest Path Faster Algorithm) only re-adds vertices when their distance improves.
// bf_detekter_neg_syklus: a V-th relaxation pass that finds improvement indicates a negative cycle.
// floyd_warshall computes fw_apsp (All-Pairs Shortest Paths) in O(V³) with DP over intermediate vertices.
// alt_heuristikk (ALT) uses landmark vertices with precomputed distances for tight A* bounds.
// ch_snarveiskant connects two vertices in a higher-order graph, bypassing contracted vertices.
// ch_spørring runs bidirectional Dijkstra upward in the contraction hierarchy from source and target.
// dfs_start_tid and dfs_slutt_tid enable topological sorting and bridge detection.
// topo_kahn uses a queue of zero in-degree vertices, removing edges as vertices are processed.
// dag_lengste_sti negates weights and runs dag_korteste_sti for critical path analysis.
// hierholzer builds an Euler circuit by repeatedly extending a partial circuit with new cycles.

// Primitive flow:
// Dijkstra: initialisér avstand[kilde]=0, alt=∞ -> sett inn i prio-kø
//   loop: trekk ut min -> for nabo v: ny_avst = avst[u]+kant(u,v)
//   ny_avst < avst[v]? -> oppdater avst[v] + sett inn v -> fortsett til mål
// Floyd-Warshall: for k in 0..V: for i in 0..V: for j in 0..V:
//   fw_matrise[i][j] = min(fw_matrise[i][j], fw_matrise[i][k]+fw_matrise[k][j])
// CH oppbygging: kontrahér noder i lavscore-orden
//   for nabo u,w: beregn korteste u-w sti via andre noder
//   kortere via snarveikant? -> legg til snarveikant(u,w)
// Topologisk: inngrad[v] for alle v -> kø alle med inngrad=0
//   pop u -> legg til ordre -> for nabo v: inngrad[v]-- -> hvis 0: legg til kø

// This defines shortest path algorithms: Dijkstra with Fibonacci/binary heaps, Bellman-Ford
// with SPFA, Floyd-Warshall APSP, A* with ALT landmarks, Contraction Hierarchies, BFS/DFS
// with timestamps, topological sort, and Eulerian circuits.

