// Semantic direction:
// nettverksflyt routes flow from nf_kilde to nf_sluk respecting edge capacities.
// nf_restgraf tracks residual capacities after sending flow.
// maks_flyt_min_snitt: the maximum flow equals the minimum cut capacity (max-flow min-cut theorem).
// edmonds_karp implements Ford-Fulkerson with BFS augmentation — O(VE²) guaranteed.
// dinic_nivågraf is the layered graph built by BFS; flow only moves to deeper layers.
// dinic_blokkerende_flyt saturates all paths in the level graph in one DFS pass — O(V²E).
// pr_høyde is a height label; flow only pushes from higher to lower vertices.
// pr_discharge repeatedly pushes all excess from an active node until it's balanced.
// pr_gap_heuristikk detects and handles gap in height labels for faster convergence.
// mcf_successive_shortest finds augmenting paths of minimum cost using shortest path with potentials.
// mcf_potensial eliminates negative-cost edges for Dijkstra applicability.
// hopcroft_karp runs BFS to find a set of augmenting paths simultaneously — O(E√V).
// ungarsk_metode solves the assignment problem (minimum cost perfect matching) in O(V³).
// blossom_algoritme handles odd-length cycles (blossoms) in general matching.
// blomst_kontraksjon shrinks a blossom to a single vertex; blomst_ekspansjon restores it.
// gale_shapley produces a stable matching where no pair prefers each other over their current partners.
// gs_mann_optimal gives each man his best achievable partner in any stable matching.
// prosjektvalg uses parametric max-flow to select projects with dependencies maximizing profit.

// Primitive flow:
// Dinic maks-flyt: repeat:
//   bfs: bygg nivågraf fra kilde -> sluk (BFS på restgraf)
//   sluk ikke nådd -> bryt (ingen augmenteringssti)
//   dfs: finn blokkerende flyt i nivågraf -> øk total flyt
// Hopcroft-Karp: repeat:
//   BFS fra alle umatchede venstre-noder -> finn korteste augmenteringsstier
//   DFS: augmentér alle funn stier i parallell
// Gale-Shapley: alle menn foreslår til sin favoritt
