// Semantic direction:
// grafpartisjonering divides graph vertices into k balanced groups minimizing gp_snitt_størrelse.
// kernighan_lin swaps pairs of vertices between partitions, keeping swaps that improve the cut.
// kl_gevinst is the reduction in cut size from swapping a vertex to the other partition.
// fiduccia_mattheyses uses a bucket priority queue for O(|E|) per pass.
// multilevel_partisjonering coarsens the graph, partitions the coarsened version, then projects back.
// metis_heavy_edge matches high-weight edge pairs for coarsening, preserving graph structure.
// modularietsgevinst is the change in modularity from merging two communities.
// louvain_fase1 moves each node to the neighbor's community that maximizes modularity gain.
// louvain_fase2 creates super_noder representing communities, then applies fase1 again.
// leiden_refinement restores internally connected communities that Louvain might overlook.
// lp_asynkron updates each node's label to the most frequent among its neighbors immediately.
// info_map_equation minimizes the description length of a random walk using the community structure.
// gn_betweenness computes edge betweenness (number of shortest paths through each edge).
// girvan_newman removes the highest-betweenness edge iteratively to reveal community structure.
// cpm_k_kliker defines communities as maximal sets of adjacent k-cliques.
// assortativity measures whether high-degree vertices tend to connect to other high-degree vertices.
// small_world_koeffisient quantifies the clustering-vs-diameter trade-off characteristic of social networks.

// Primitive flow:
// Louvain: initialisér: hvert node i sin community
//   fase1: for hvert node v: flytt til nabo-community med størst ΔQ
//   gjenta til ingen forbedring -> fase2: kontraher communities til super-noder
//   gjenta til konvergens
// Label propagation: for hvert node (tilfeldig orden):
//   tell nabos etiketter -> velg flertall -> oppdater node-etikett
//   gjenta til ingen endringer
// Infomap: minimer L = Σ_modules q_i * H(module_i) + (n-1)*H(module_exit)
//   gradient-fri optimalisering via random walk på community-grafen
// Girvan-Newman: beregn betweenness for alle kanter -> fjern høyest
//   re-beregn betweenness -> gjenta -> registrer dendrogram -> kutt for beste Q

// This defines graph partitioning and community detection: Kernighan-Lin, Fiduccia-Mattheyses,
// multilevel METIS, Louvain/Leiden modularity optimization, label propagation, Infomap,
// Girvan-Newman betweenness, overlapping communities, and network quality metrics.

