// Semantic direction:
// konvolusjon slides conv_kjerner over spatial dimensions, computing dot products.
// conv_dilasjon inserts zeros between kernel elements, increasing receptive field without extra params.
// conv_grupper divides channels into groups; depthwise_conv uses grupper=innkanaler.
// separerbar_conv: depthwise (spatial) then pointwise (channel mixing) — efficient approximation.
// resnet_blokk uses residual connections to train hundreds of layers without degradation.
// resnet_bottleneck uses 1×1 conv to reduce channels before and after 3×3 conv.
// dense_blokk connects each layer to all subsequent layers, reusing features fully.
// efficientnet compound_skalering simultaneously scales depth, width, and resolution.
// inverted_residual (MobileNet v2) expands channels then applies depthwise conv.
// squeeze_excitation recalibrates channel responses using global average pooling.
// feature_pyramid_network builds multi-scale feature maps for detecting objects at all sizes.
// anchor_boks is a pre-defined box shape; RPN predicts offsets and objectness scores.
// unet symmetrically encodes then decodes, using skip_connection_seg to preserve spatial detail.
// atrous_conv (dilated) enlarges the receptive field without downsampling in deeplab_v3.
// aspp_modul applies atrous convolutions at multiple rates to capture multi-scale context.
// mixup trains on convex combinations of pairs: x̃ = λx_i + (1-λ)x_j.
// cutmix pastes rectangular patches from one image into another with mixed labels.

// Primitive flow:
// ResNet-50 fremoverpass: inndata(3×224×224)
//   conv1(64, 7×7, steg=2) → bn → relu → maxpool(3×3, steg=2)
//   layer1-4: residual_blokk * N → global_gjennomsnitt_pooling → FC(1000) → softmax
// Feature Pyramid: C3,C4,C5 fra ResNet
//   P5=conv1x1(C5) → P4=upsample(P5)+conv1x1(C4) → P3=upsample(P4)+conv1x1(C3)
//   fpn_lateral fusion → multi-skala feature kart for detektor-hodet
// DepthwiseSeparable: 3×3×Cin×Cout standard conv -> splitt:
//   3×3×1×Cin depthwise (Cin filtre à 3×3×1) + 1×1×Cin×Cout pointwise
//   FLOP-reduksjon: 8-9× for typiske nettverk

// This defines CNNs: convolution variants (dilated, depthwise, separable), pooling, ResNet/
// DenseNet/EfficientNet/MobileNet architectures, attention (SE/CBAM), object detection
// (FPN/RetinaNet/DETR), semantic segmentation (U-Net/DeepLab), and data augmentation.

