// Semantic direction:
// data_parallellisme replicates the model on each device and shards the mini-batch.
// dp_all_reduce averages gradients across all devices before each optimizer step.
// ring_all_reduce passes partial reductions around a ring, achieving O(N) communication.
// powersgd compresses gradients via low-rank factorization for bandwidth-efficient syncing.
// modell_parallellisme splits the model itself across devices for models too large for one GPU.
// tp_kolonne_paralell splits weight matrices column-wise; each device handles a column partition.
// tp_rad_parallell splits row-wise; requires an all-reduce after the matrix multiply.
// pipeline_parallellisme assigns different layers to different devices.
// pp_1f1b_plan (one-forward-one-backward) reduces pipeline pp_boble (idle time).
// pp_interleaved uses virtual_pipeline_steg to further reduce bubble overhead.
// fsdp_full_shard shards parameters, gradients, AND optimizer state (equivalent to ZeRO-3).
// fsdp_prefetch loads the next module's parameters while the current module computes.
// zero_cpu_offload moves optimizer state to CPU RAM to fit larger models on GPU.
// 3d_parallellisme combines data/tensor/pipeline parallelism across a 3D device mesh.
// ring_oppmerksomhet_3d partitions the sequence dimension for near-linear context scaling.
// async_grad_synk overlaps backward pass computation with gradient communication.
// grad_klar_hook triggers gradient communication as soon as each bucket is ready.
// local_sgd averages parameters every H steps — reduces communication frequency.

// Primitive flow:
// DDP (data parallel): for hvert steg:
//   frem-pass(lokal batch) -> tap -> bak-pass -> gradient
//   ring_all_reduce(gradient) -> alle enheter har gjennomsnitt
//   optimizer.steg() -> parameter oppdatert identisk på alle enheter
// FSDP steg: parameter shard gjenoppbygg (all-gather) før lag
//   frem-pass -> frigi parameter shard (minne tilbake)
//   bak-pass -> gjenoppbygg shard for grad -> reduce-scatter grads
//   optimizer: oppdater lokalt shard av param
// 3D parallell: N GPUs = dp × tp × pp
//   tp-grupper kommuniserer hyppig (in-node NVLink)
//   pp-grupper kommuniserer mellom noder (per pipeline-steg)
//   dp synkroniserer sjeldnere (hvert grad_akkum_steg)

// This defines distributed training: data parallelism with ring-allreduce and PowerSGD,
// tensor and pipeline parallelism (1F1B/interleaved), FSDP with CPU offload, ZeRO stages,
// 3D parallelism with ring attention for long context, async gradient synchronization,
// and distributed checkpointing.

