// Semantic direction:
// avhengige_typer allow types to depend on values — the foundation of proof assistants.
// pi_type_dt Π(x:A).B(x) is both the type of functions (when B doesn't depend on x) and universal quantifiers.
// sigma_type_dt Σ(x:A).B(x) is both dependent pairs and existential quantifiers.
// univers_i is a type of types at level i; univers_suksessor(i) is the next universe level.
// kumulativitet: if A : Uᵢ then A : Uᵢ₊₁ — smaller universes are contained in larger ones.
// type_in_type collapses the hierarchy, leading to Girard's paradox (inconsistency).
// induktiv_type_dt is defined by its konstruktøre and the eliminasjon_prinsipp (recursion scheme).
// strikt_positiv requires the type being defined not to appear to the left of any arrow in constructors.
// vektor_type Vek(A, n) has exactly n elements of type A — the length is part of the type.
// vektor_head : Π(n:ℕ).Vek(A, n+1) → A — head is only defined for non-empty vectors, proven by type.
// transport_dt: if x=y in A, then any P(x) can be transported to P(y).
// avhengig_eliminasjon allows the return type of a match to depend on the matched value.
// motive_type is the type family P that the elimination gives.
// calculus_of_constructions unifies types and terms in a single universe.
// cubical_type_teori gives a constructive interpretation of univalence and higher inductive types.
// hcomp provides a way to compose paths, enabling the full power of HoTT computationally.

// Primitive flow:
// Vek append: append : Π(n m:ℕ). Vek(A,n) → Vek(A,m) → Vek(A, n+m)
//   append n m nil v = v                      -- 0+m = m (definitionally)
//   append n m (cons x xs) v = cons x (append (n-1) m xs v)
//   retur type: n+m automatisk bevart via typesjekkeren
// Transport: eq : x=y i A, P : A→Type, px : P(x) -> transport(eq, px) : P(y)
//   J-eliminasjon: beviser P(x,x,refl) -> P(x,y,eq) for alle y,eq
// Sigma eliminering: p : Σ(n:ℕ).Vek(A,n) -> la (n, v) = p i v : Vek(A,n)
//   n og v er koblede: typen til v avhenger av n

// This defines dependent types: Π/Σ types with full elimination rules, universe hierarchy
// with cumulativity, inductive types (Peano/vectors) with dependent elimination, transport
// and congruence, the Calculus of Constructions, and Cubical Type Theory with hcomp.

