// Semantic direction:
// hindley_milner is the foundation of type inference in ML-family languages.
// hm_algoritme_w synthesizes a type for expressions, accumulating substitutions.
// hm_let_regel: let x = e₁ in e₂ — generalize the type of e₁ before typing e₂.
// hm_gen_regel closes over free type variables to create a type_skjema (∀ α. τ).
// hm_inst_regel instantiates a type_skjema with fresh type variables for each use.
// most_general_unifier is the unique most-general substitution solving a unification problem.
// occur_sjekk_ti prevents infinite types: a type variable α cannot occur in the type it unifies with.
// begrensningsbasert_inferens separates constraint generation from solving for better error messages.
// bidireksjonell_type_sjekking alternates between inferens (synthesize a type) and sjekking (check against a given type).
// bi_switch moves between modes: synthesized types are checked against the expected type.
// pierce_turner is the original presentation of bidirectional type checking.
// lokal_type_inferens restricts type information propagation for predictable inference.
// mode_switching: explicit type annotations trigger sjekking_modus for better inference.
// jones_inferens handles type class constraints in the presence of polymorphism.
// defaulting resolves ambiguous class constraints by picking a default type.
// miller_unifikasjon solves higher-order unification for simply-typed patterns.
// pattern_unifikasjon is decidable subset of higher-order unification handling λ-patterns.
// blame_calculus tracks type errors to the source of incorrect type annotations.

// Primitive flow:
// Algoritme W: W(Γ, x) = (id, inst(Γ(x)))  -- instansiér type-skjema
//   W(Γ, λx.e) = let (S, τ) = W(Γ∪{x:α}, e)  -- ny type-var α for x
//               in (S, S(α)→τ)
//   W(Γ, e₁ e₂) = let (S₁,τ₁) = W(Γ, e₁); (S₂,τ₂) = W(S₁(Γ), e₂)
//                 in (mgu(S₂(τ₁), τ₂→α) ∘ S₂ ∘ S₁, α)
//   W(Γ, let x=e₁ in e₂) = generalisér type, bind til x, inferer e₂
// Bidireksjonell: Γ ⊢ e ⇒ τ (infer) vs Γ ⊢ e ⇐ τ (check)
//   λx.e ⇐ τ₁→τ₂: sjekk e ⇐ τ₂ med x:τ₁ i Γ
//   λx.e ⇒ feil: trenger annoteringeller forventet type
//   e ⇒ τ og τ=τ': OK | τ≠τ': subsumpsjon/feil

// This defines type inference: Hindley-Milner algorithm W with generalization/instantiation,
// Robinson unification with occur check, constraint-based inference, bidirectional type
// checking (Pierce-Turner), type class inference with defaulting, and higher-order
// pattern unification for dependently-typed systems.

