// Semantic direction:
// sesjon_typer describe communication protocols between concurrent processes.
// st_send ?T.S means: receive a value of type T, then continue with session S.
// st_motta !T.S means: send a value of type T, then continue with session S.
// st_velg ⊕{l:S} means: choose a label l and continue with the corresponding session.
// st_tilby &{l:S} means: offer choices; the peer selects which branch to take.
// dual_sesjon: the dual of ?T.S is !T.(dual S); send and receive are swapped.
// lineær_kanal ensures each channel endpoint is used exactly once — no aliasing.
// mu_type_st enables recursive session protocols: μX. S where S may refer to X.
// pi_kalkulus is the process calculus underlying session types.
// pi_ny (νx)(P) creates a private channel x scoped to P.
// pi_parallell P|Q runs P and Q concurrently with access to shared names.
// mps_global_type describes the full conversation from a bird's-eye view.
// mps_projeksjon extracts a participant's local view from the global type.
// mps_kompatibilitet checks that local types are consistent projections of the global.
// scribble_protokoll is a practical notation for multiparty session types.
// asynkron_send places a message in a queue without waiting for the receiver.
// st_subtype: T₁ ≤ T₂ means T₁ can be used where T₂ is expected.
// input_contravariant: if T₁ ≤ T₂ then ?T₂.S ≤ ?T₁.S (contravariant in input type).
// runtime_kontroll_st: verifies session adherence at runtime when static typing is unavailable.

// Primitive flow:
// Definér protokoll: type Banktjeneste = ?Int.!Bool.End  -- motta beløp, send OK/NEI
//   server: fn serve(k: Banktjeneste) { la (beløp, k2) = recv(k); send(k2, beløp<saldo) }
//   klient: fn kjøp(k: dual(Banktjeneste)) { let k2 = send(k, 100); let (ok, _) = recv(k2) }
// Dual garanterer kommunikasjonssamsvar: server og klient er kompatible ved konstruksjon
// Multiparti: global type G = Kjøper → Selger: Pris. Selger → Kjøper: Aksept. End
//   prosjektér på Kjøper: !Pris.?Aksept.End
//   prosjektér på Selger: ?Pris.!Aksept.End
// Rekursiv protokoll: μX. ?Int.(!Bool.X ⊕ End) -- gjenta til ferdig

// This defines session types: binary and multiparty protocols, duality, linear channel usage,
// π-calculus process calculus, Scribble global/local type projection, asynchronous sessions,
// dependent and refinement session types, session subtyping, and deadlock-free communication.

