// Semantic direction:
// adjunksjoner are ubiquitous dualities: F ⊣ G means Hom(F(A), B) ≅ Hom(A, G(B)) naturally.
// adj_enhet η: Id → GF — the unit shows how to inject into the adjunction.
// adj_koenhet ε: FG → Id — the counit shows how to project out.
// adj_triangelidentiteter: (Gε)(ηG) = id_G and (εF)(Fη) = id_F.
// fri_glemsom: the free group functor is left adjoint to the forgetful functor to sets.
// monad_fra_adjunksjon: M = GF with unit η and multiplication GεF: GFGF → GF.
// kleisli_kategori has the same objects as C; morphisms A→B are C-morphisms A→M(B).
// eilenberg_moore_kategori has M-algebras as objects — the "canonical" way to resolve the adjunction.
// monad_lover: (μ∘Mμ = μ∘μM) and (μ∘ηM = id = μ∘Mη).
// monoidal_kategori has a tensor product ⊗ with a unit object, associator, and unitors.
// mac_lane_koherens_kt: all diagrams built from associators and unitors commute.
// kartesisk_lukket kategori has products and exponential objects — models simply-typed λ-calculus.
// enriched_kategori replaces hom-sets with objects from a monoidal category V.
// ab_enriched: hom-objects are abelian groups — the setting for homological algebra.
// venstre_kan_extension Lan_K F is the universal functor extending F along K.
// coend_integral ∫^C F(C,C) is the "sum over C" of F's diagonal.
// ninja_yoneda: F(A) ≅ ∫^C Hom(A,C) ⊗ F(C) — the co-end formula for Yoneda.

// Primitive flow:
// Adjunksjon sjekk F ⊣ G: for alle A,B:
//   Hom(FA, B) ≅ Hom(A, GB) -- naturlig i A og B
//   enhet: η_A : A → GFA (universal morfisme fra A)
//   koenhet: ε_B : FGB → B (universal morfisme til B)
// State monad: M = (S→) ∘ (×S): M A = S → (A × S)
//   η_A(a) = λs. (a, s)  -- retur
//   μ_A(m) = λs. let (m', s') = m s in m' s'  -- join
//   lover: μ∘η = id, μ∘Mη = id, μ∘μ = μ∘Mμ
// Kan extension Lan_K F(D): = colim_{K(C)→D} F(C)
//   universell: alle G med GK ≅ F faktoriserer gjennom Lan_K F

// This defines adjunctions with triangle identities, free-forgetful adjunctions, monads from
// adjunctions (Kleisli/Eilenberg-Moore), programming monads (State/Reader/Writer/IO), comonads,
// monoidal categories with MacLane coherence, enriched categories, Kan extensions, and ends/coends.

