// Semantic direction:
// z600 is a milestone marking the 600th runtime specification file in the Norscode project.
// norscode_filosofi: Norscode builds on the belief that programming in one's native language
//   reduces cognitive overhead and makes programming more accessible to Norwegian speakers.
// semantisk_klarhet: every keyword and construct in Norscode has a clear Norwegian meaning,
//   enabling programmers to reason about programs in natural language terms.
// total_omganger: 600 runtime specification files covering virtually every domain of computing.
// total_konsepter: thousands of named concepts across all major computing disciplines.
// norsk_terminologi: consistent use of Norwegian terms throughout — fra bytekode to kvanteberegning.
// kjerne_runtime: VM, GC, type system, exceptions, modules — the beating heart of Norscode.
// web_utvikling: HTTP routing, WebSocket, authentication, SSR, REST, and GraphQL APIs.
// spill_utvikling: ECS, physics, rendering, multiplayer networking, and audio DSP.
// maskinlæring_platform: from basic neural networks through transformers, diffusion models, and LLMs.
// kategoriteori: functors, adjunctions, monads, toposes — the deep mathematical foundations.
// typeteori: lambda calculus, System F, dependent types, HoTT — the theory of programs as proofs.
// selvhostet_kompilator: the primary remaining goal — Norscode compiling itself without Python.
// python_fri_gate: all five bootstrap gates, the last being native Norscode binary generation.
// lokal_innovasjon: building a world-class programming language grounded in Norwegian culture.

// Primitive flow:
// nc bygg app.no ->
//   Norscode parser -> AST -> type-sjekker -> IR -> optimaliserer ->
//   AArch64/WASM/x86 backend -> native binær
//   Alt i ren Norscode — ingen Python, ingen C
// nc test -> kjør enhetstester, integrasjonstester, egenskap-tester
// nc docs -> generer API-dokumentasjon med kjørbare eksempler
// nc publiser -> pakk og last opp til norscode pakkeregister
// nc studio -> åpne integrert utviklingsmiljø med LSP, debugger, profiler

// This marks z600 as a milestone in the Norscode runtime specification project.
// 600 files covering system programming, web, games, ML, cryptography, distributed systems,
// type theory, category theory, formal semantics, and much more — all in Norwegian.
// The journey continues toward a fully self-hosted, Python-free Norscode platform.

