// Semantic direction:
// program_ekvivalens defines when two programs are interchangeable in all contexts.
// operasjonell_semantikk gives the meaning of programs as sequences of computation steps.
// storstegs_semantikk directly relates programs to their final values (big-step).
// liten_stegs_semantikk shows each individual reduction step (small-step).
// konvergens_observasjon: observe whether a program terminates with a result.
// kontekstuell_ekvivalens_pe: e₁ ≅_ctx e₂ if C[e₁] and C[e₂] have identical observations.
// bisimulasjon: R is a bisimulation if whenever (p,q)∈R, p and q can simulate each other's steps.
// svak_bisimulasjon ignores τ (silent) transitions — the standard notion for process equivalence.
// bisimulasjon_kongruens: bisimulation is preserved by all context operations.
// denotasjonell_sunnhet: if ⟦e₁⟧ = ⟦e₂⟧ then e₁ ≅_ctx e₂ (denotational equality implies contextual).
// operasjonell_adekvans: if e₁ ≅_ctx e₂ then ⟦e₁⟧ = ⟦e₂⟧ (contextual implies denotational).
// pcf_full_abstraksjon: both directions hold for PCF — proven via game semantics.
// cbpv_full_abstraksjon: Call-by-Push-Value achieves full abstraction more directly.
// coinduktiv_bisimulasjon enables bisimulation proofs on infinite/corecursive programs.
// observasjonell_refinement: e₁ refines e₂ if e₁ may-implies e₂ (more defined behavior).
// kompilerings_korrekthet: a compiler is correct if it preserves observational equivalence.

// Primitive flow:
// Kontekstuell ekvivalens-bevis: vis e₁ ≅_ctx e₂ via logisk relasjon
//   definer LR_T slik at (v₁,v₂) ∈ LR_T -> v₁ og v₂ er obs-ekvivalente ved T
//   fundamentalt lemma: ⊢e:T -> (⟦e⟧, ⟦e⟧) ∈ LR_T
//   korollar: e₁ ≅_ctx e₂ gdde (⟦e₁⟧, ⟦e₂⟧) ∈ LR_T
// Bisimulasjon-bevis for prosess-kalkulus:
//   vis kandidatrelasjon R er en bisimulasjon:
//   for alle (P,Q) ∈ R: P → P' => ∃Q': Q → Q' og (P',Q') ∈ R (og vice versa)
//   korollar: P ~ Q (bisimilær) => P ≅ Q (kontekstuelt ekvivalente)
// Kompileringskorrekthet: vis at for alle kildeprogram e:
//   C(e₁) ≅_target C(e₂) dersom e₁ ≅_source e₂
//   typisk via backing-translation / simulation-argument

// This defines the relationship between operational and denotational semantics: observational
// equivalence, contextual equivalence, bisimulation (weak/strong), congruence, full abstraction
// (soundness and adequacy), effects on equivalence notions, coinductive bisimulation proofs,
// and compiler correctness as semantic preservation.

