// Semantic direction:
// enriched_kategoriteori replaces hom-sets with objects of a monoidal base category V.
// v_hom(A,B) is an object of V rather than a set; composition is a V-morphism.
// ab_kategori has hom-groups (abelian groups) — the setting for homological algebra.
// preadditive_kategori: hom-sets are abelian groups and composition is bilinear.
// abelian_kategori has all finite limits and colimits, kernels, cokernels — perfect for homology.
// lawvere_metric interprets [0,∞]-enriched categories as generalized metric spaces.
// metrisk_distanse d(A,B) satisfies: d(A,A)=0, d(A,C) ≤ d(A,B)+d(B,C).
// 2_kategori enriches over Cat — morphisms between morphisms (natural transformations).
// bicategori weakens 2-category composition to be associative and unital only up to iso.
// pseudofunktor preserves composition and identities up to coherent isomorphism.
// enriched_yoneda_embedding: A ↦ V(−,A) is fully faithful in any V-category.
// weighted_limit generalizes ordinary limits to weighted diagrams in V-categories.
// grothendieck_fibrasjon: a functor p:E→B is a fibration if every morphism in B has a cartesian lift.
// cloven_fibrasjon has a chosen lift for each morphism — splitting the fibration.
// ind_kategori is the free completion of C under filtered colimits.
// graded_monads_ek: monads enriched over a quantale, generalizing graded type systems.
// quantale_enriched: hom-objects from a complete lattice with a monoid structure.

// Primitive flow:
// Ab-kategori komposisjon: f:A→B og g:B→C og h:A→C
//   (g+g') ∘ f = g∘f + g'∘f  -- bilinearitet (distribuerer over sum)
//   f ∘ (g+g') = f∘g + f∘g'  -- begge sider
// Lawvere metrisk: kategori beriket over ([0,∞], ≥, +, 0)
//   V(A,B) = d(A,B) ∈ [0,∞]
//   komposisjon: d(A,C) ≤ d(A,B) + d(B,C) (triangle ulikhet)
//   identitet: d(A,A) ≤ 0 -> d(A,A) = 0
// Grothendieck fibrasjon: p:E→B
//   for morfisme f:X→Y i B og objekt U over Y (pU=Y)
//   eksisterer kartesiansk løft f*U → U over f
// 2-kategorisk naturlighet: α: F ⇒ G mellom 2-funktorer
//   for 2-morfisme θ: f ⇒ g i C:
//   Gθ ∘ αf = αg ∘ Fθ  -- 2-dimensional naturalitetsbetingelse

// This defines enriched category theory: V-categories with examples (Ab/metric/2-Cat),
// enriched Yoneda with weighted limits, bicategories with pseudo-functors and modifications,
// Grothendieck fibrations, ind/pro completions, and applications to graded monads and
// quantale-enriched categories for substructural type systems.

