// Semantic direction:
// algebraiske_effekter: effects as algebraic operations with handlers that interpret them.
//   perform Read() resumes with a value; handler decides what value to supply.
// effekt_operasjon: an operation signature like Read : () → Int; Write : String → ().
// effekt_behandler: a first-class value that gives meaning to each operation.
// dypt_behandler: handles all recursive calls too — the entire computation is wrapped.
// grunt_behandler: handles one layer at a time; inner effects still need outer handlers.
// effekt_rader: typed effect rows like {Read, Write, Exn | ρ} — open rows via polymorphism.
// one_shot_effekter: continuation is invoked at most once (like exceptions, early return).
// multi_shot_effekter: continuation can be invoked multiple times (like nondeterminism, backtracking).
// kontinuasjons_semantikk: algebraic effects are operationally equivalent to delimited continuations.
// graded_effekt: effects annotated with extra information — graded monads for effect quantification.
// koka_effekter: Koka language pioneered row-based effect types; OCaml 5 adds native effect handlers.

// Primitive flow:
// effekt Les { hent : () -> Tekst }
// effekt Skriv { put : Tekst -> () }
// behandle program med
//   Les.hent() => k => k("input")
//   Skriv.put(s) => k => { skriv(s); k(()) }

