// Semantic direction:
// realiserbarhet: a program e realizes proposition P if e witnesses P's truth computationally.
//   Kleene: e ⊩ A∧B means (e)₀ ⊩ A and (e)₁ ⊩ B; e ⊩ A→B means ∀a.(a ⊩ A → {e}(a) ⊩ B).
// kleene_realiserbarhet: Kleene (1945) — the first realizability interpretation of intuitionistic logic.
// effektiv_topos: Hyland (1982) — a topos where all morphisms are computable (PERs over ℕ).
// churchs_tese: every effectively computable function is Turing-computable.
// aritmetisk_hierarki: Σ⁰ₙ/Π⁰ₙ classify definability by alternating quantifiers over ℕ.
// halting_problem: no Turing machine can decide if an arbitrary TM halts — diagonal argument.
// rice_teorem: all non-trivial semantic properties of programs are undecidable.
// turing_jump: from degree d, the jump d' has d'= halting problem relative to d.
// PER_modell: partial equivalence relations over ℕ model types in realizability models.
// kreativt_sett: a c.e. set so productive it can simulate all c.e. sets — complete Σ⁰₁.

// Primitive flow:
// beregnbarhet: f : ℕ → ℕ er beregnbar ⟺ ∃ Turing-maskin M: ∀n. M(n) = f(n)
// realiserbarhet: n ⊩ ∀x.∃y.P(x,y) ⟺ ∀x. {n}(x) ↓ ∧ {n}(x) ⊩ ∃y.P(x,y)

