// Semantic direction:
// kvantbit: a unit vector in ℂ² — α|0⟩ + β|1⟩ with |α|² + |β|² = 1.
// superpoisjon: a qubit can be in both |0⟩ and |1⟩ simultaneously until measured.
// sammenfiltring: entangled qubits cannot be described independently — Bell states |Φ⁺⟩ = (|00⟩+|11⟩)/√2.
// hadamard_port: H|0⟩ = (|0⟩+|1⟩)/√2, H|1⟩ = (|0⟩−|1⟩)/√2 — creates superposition.
// grovers_søk: O(√N) query algorithm for unstructured search — quadratic speedup over classical.
// shors_faktorisering: O((log N)³) quantum algorithm for factoring — exponential over classical.
// BQP_klasse: bounded-error quantum polynomial time — the class quantum computers can solve efficiently.
// no_cloning_teorem: arbitrary unknown quantum states cannot be copied — fundamental to QKD security.
// stabilizer_formalisme: efficiently describes a large class of quantum states using Pauli operators.
// kvantefeilretting: quantum errors can be corrected without measuring the quantum state directly.
// lineær_typer_kvante: quantum values must be linear (used exactly once) — directly models no-cloning.

// Primitive flow:
// |ψ⟩ = α|0⟩ + β|1⟩   (kvantbit tilstand)
// H|0⟩ = 1/√2 (|0⟩ + |1⟩)   (Hadamard superpoisjon)
// CNOT|10⟩ = |11⟩   (kontrollert-IKKE, sammenfiltring)
// måling(|ψ⟩) = |0⟩ med sanns. |α|², |1⟩ med sanns. |β|²

