// Semantic direction:
// SSA_form: every variable assigned exactly once; φ-nodes merge values at control flow joins.
// Cytron_algoritme: places φ-nodes at iterated dominance frontiers — minimal SSA in O(n α(n)).
// dominans_grenser: DF(n) = {y | n dominates a predecessor of y but not y itself} — key for SSA.
// registerallokering: NP-complete (graph colouring), but linear scan is O(n) and good enough.
// Chaitin_allokering: Chaitin (1981) — graph colouring with spilling; foundational for optimising compilers.
// BURS_tiling: bottom-up rewrite system — optimal instruction selection via dynamic programming on trees.
// software_pipelining: overlap iterations of a loop — expose instruction-level parallelism across iterations.
// inlining_beslutning: inline if benefit (eliminate call overhead + enable further opts) > code size cost.
// polymorfisk_inline_cache: V8/JVM technique — cache the last seen type at a call site for fast dispatch.
// deoptimering: when a speculation fails at runtime, revert JIT code to interpreter — needed for correctness.
// MLIR_dialekter: composable IR dialects in LLVM's MLIR framework — enables progressive lowering.

// Primitive flow:
// kildekode → frontend (parse/type) → SSA-IR → optimaliseringer → instruksjonsvalg
//           → registerallokering → instruksjonsplanlegging → maskinkode

