// Semantic direction:
// Ramsey_teori: in any sufficiently large structure, order must appear — R(3,3)=6 means any
//   2-colouring of K₆ contains a monochromatic triangle.
// probabilistisk_metode_Ramsey: Erdős (1947) — random colouring shows R(k,k) > 2^{k/2}.
// regularitet_lemma: Szemerédi (1975) — any graph can be partitioned into k parts where almost
//   all pairs are pseudo-random (ε-regular) — foundational for graph limits.
// ekspandergraf: sparse, highly connected graphs — fundamental for derandomisation and coding theory.
// Cheeger_ulikhet: h(G)/2 ≤ λ₁ ≤ √(2h(G)) — eigenvalue gap controls expansion.
// ramanujan_grafer: (d,λ)-expanders where λ ≤ 2√(d−1) — optimal spectral gap; constructed via number theory.
// zigzag_produkt: Reingold-Vadhan-Wigderson (2000) — combine small and large expanders; key for PSPACE=L proof.
// Robertson_Seymour: every minor-closed family has a finite set of forbidden minors — proved over 23 papers.
// triangle_removal_lemma: if a graph has ε-fraction triangles, it's ε-close to a triangle-free graph.
// spektral_mixing: random walk on expander mixes in O(log n / spectral gap) steps.

// Primitive flow:
// ekspansjonstesting: φ(S) = |E(S, V\S)| / min(|S|, |V\S|)
// Cheeger: φ(G) ≥ λ₁/2 der λ₁ er nest minste egenverdi av Laplacian
// Ramsey: ∀farging av K_{R(s,t)} → ∃ monokromatisk K_s eller K_t

