// Semantic direction:
// PAC_læring: Valiant (1984) — a learner PAC-learns C if for any ε,δ>0, using m(ε,δ) samples
//   it outputs h with P[error(h) > ε] < δ; m must be polynomial in 1/ε, 1/δ, size(C).
// VC_dimensjon: the largest set a hypothesis class can shatter — fundamental measure of capacity.
// Sauer_Shelah_lemma: growth function Π_H(m) ≤ Σᵢ₌₀ᵈ C(m,i) = O(mᵈ) where d=VC(H).
// fundamental_teorem_SL: H is PAC learnable iff VCdim(H) < ∞ — a beautiful characterisation.
// Rademacher_kompleksitet: expected correlation of H with random ±1 labels — data-dependent capacity.
// dobbel_nedsenkningsfenomen: error decreases, increases (overfit), then decreases again past interpolation threshold.
// bias_varians_dekomposisjon: E[(ŷ−y)²] = Bias² + Variance + irreducible noise.
// McDiarmid_ulikhet: if f changes by at most cᵢ when xᵢ changes — P[f > Ef + t] ≤ exp(−2t²/Σcᵢ²).
// Mercer_teorem: k(x,y) is a valid kernel iff the Gram matrix is positive semi-definite for all data.
// regret_analyse: online learner regret = Σloss(hₜ) − min_h Σloss(h) — sublinear is good.

// Primitive flow:
// PAC_prøve: m ≥ (1/ε)(ln|H| + ln(1/δ)) prøver er nok for konsistent læring (finite H)
// VC_grense: m ≥ O((d log(1/ε) + log(1/δ))/ε) der d = VCdim(H)
// Rademacher: R_S(H) = E_σ[sup_{h∈H} (1/m)Σσᵢh(xᵢ)] — mål på overfit-kapasitet

